genresAdvancedInfo.name: jazz chileno
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Jazz Chileno is a genre of jazz that developed in Chile in the 1950s and 60s. It incorporates elements of traditional Chilean music, such as the cueca and the chacarera, with jazz improvisation and instrumentation. Expect to hear a lot of guitar, piano, and saxophone in Jazz Chileno, as well as a focus on rhythm and melody.
